				\begin{document}$$\begin{array}{c}{\rm{mean}}({\rm{density}}) \sim {\rm{s}}(\mathrm{ln}({\rm{depth}}))+{\rm{s}}({\rm{mean}}({\rm{SS}}))+{\rm{s}}({\rm{mean}}({\rm{BT}}))\\ \quad +\,{\rm{s}}({\rm{mean}}({\rm{BS}}))+{\rm{factor}}({\rm{season}})\end{array}$$\end{document}mean(density)~s(ln(depth))+s(mean(SS))+s(mean(BT))+s(mean(BS))+factor(season)where s is a thin-plate regression spline. Maximum degrees of freedom for each smoother were set to 4 to avoid overly “wiggly” response curves that may not be ecologically meaningful. The penalty per degree of freedom in the smoothing parameter estimation function was multiplied by a constant 1.4, as suggested by Wood40 and Kim and Gu49, to avoid overfitting.
